    ControlPanel
    - Control Panel - 1 Motor
    ControlPanelControlCommand
    Command that allows the gamepad to control the ControlPanel by using the gamepad's stick rotation.
    ControlPanelRotateCommand
    Command that allows the ControlPanel to rotate a certain number of times (assuming the encoder is set to return rotations) by tuning error.
    ControlPanelStopCommand
    Stop the control panel.
    DoNothingAuton
    Classic first auton.
    Drivetrain
    Standard drivetrain subsystem.
    DrivetrainAlignCommand
    Command in which rather than defining the direction of the robot, errors are defined and a controller is used to get the drivetrain to that point.
    DrivetrainCommand
    This is the base class for drivetrain commands.
    DrivetrainDriveCommand
    Controls the drivetrain with the gamepad with filtering.
    DrivetrainGoalCommand
    Drivetrain command to align with the goal.
    FilteredVStream
    Supplier interface for Vector2D.
    GearController
    Abstract class for implementations of gear shifting algorithms.
    GearController.Gear
    Enumeration for gear states.
    GearSwitch
    Basic implementation of a gear switching algorithm.
    Intake  
    IntakeAcquireCommand
    Instant command that sets the intake to acquire.
    IntakeAcquireWhileCommand
    Intake command to acquire and then stop (presumably used with a gamepad)
    IntakeDeacquireCommand
    Instant command that sets the intake to acquire.
    IntakeDeacquireWhileCommand
    Intake command to deacquire and then stop (presumably used with a gamepad)
    IntakeStopCommand
    Instant command to stop the intake

    Robot
    The VM is configured to automatically run this class, and to call the functions corresponding to each mode, as described in the TimedRobot documentation.
    RobotContainer
    This class is where the bulk of the robot should be declared.
    Shooter  
    ShooterStopCommand
    Sets the target RPM to 0 and stops the motors.
    ShooterTuneCommand
    Uses PID tuning to set the motors of the shooter (and feeder) to a target RPM.
    ShooterUpdateCommand
    Sets the target RPM of the shooter.
    SwerveModuleSubsystem
    This is an abstract implementation for a Swerve Module.
    SwervetrainCommand
    Abstract swerve command for a swervetrain.
    SwervetrainSubsystem
    A swervable drivetrain intended for four modules in each corner.
